comments.name: RT138A
comments.text: E138A is a common polymorphic accessory mutation weakly selected in patients receiving ETR and RPV. It reduces ETR and RPV susceptibility ~2-fold. It has a weight of 1.5 in the Tibotec ETR genotypic susceptibility score.

comments.name: RT179I
comments.text: V179I is a polymorphic mutation that is frequently selected in patients receiving ETR and RPV. But It has little, if any, direct effect on NNRTI susceptibility.

comments.name: RT238R
comments.text: K238R is a common polymorphism that does not reduce NNRTI susceptibility.

comments.name: RPVLow
comments.text: This virus is predicted to have low-level reduced susceptibility to RPV. The use of the combination of CAB/RPV should be considered to be relatively contraindicated.
